Brazil Central Bank Says Commodity Prices Up 7.83% in September

-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 
2011-10-05T15:34:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/brazil-central-bank-says-commodity-prices-up-7-83-in-september.html
Brazil ’s central bank estimates
commodity prices rose 7.83 percent in September from August,
according to a report posted on the bank’s website today.  Commodities prices rose 24.77 percent from a year earlier,
the report said.  The index is based on a basket of international commodities
that the central bank considers most relevant to Brazilian
consumer prices.  Agricultural commodities tracked by the index include beef,
cotton, soy, wheat, sugar, corn, coffee and pork. Metals include
aluminum, iron-ore, copper, tin, zinc, lead and nickel. Energy
commodities include crude oil, natural gas and coal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Harry Maurer at 
 hmaurer@bloomberg.net  